Rudd may have the ability to maintain trade and military ties with Trump, according to ABC News. The Australian Financial Review notes that Rudd and Senator Penny Wong are working to strengthen ties with Trump in the wake of the election. China's President Xi Jinping is also observing the US election closely, according to POLITICO Europe. Trump's daughter-in-law, Lara Trump, has criticized Rudd, suggesting that Australia should consider replacing him as Ambassador to the US, as reported by the Daily Mail and Sky News Australia. In an attempt to improve relations, Rudd has removed anti-Trump comments from the internet, as reported by Barron's and The Sydney Morning Herald.
